Melancholie der Engel () is a 2009 German experimental independent underground guerilla dramatic art film directed, shot, and edited by Marian Dora and cowritten by Dora and Carsten Frank (under the pseudonym Frank Oliver, used due to artistic disagreements over content with Dora which caused Frank to stop collaborating with him and around thirty minutes of footage, dealing with necrophilia, to be cut from the film).
It was planned since 2003 though shooting was delayed due to monetary issues and premiered at Weekend of Fear Festival in Erlangen and Nuremberg, Middle Franconia, Franconia, Bavaria, Germany, on 1 May 2009 (and was also screened at New York International Independent Film and Video Festival in New York, New York, United States, on 27 October 2009 and at BUT Film Festival on 7 June 2013 while the DVD got released on 30 July 2010 in Austria).
